</div>
<div class="comment" id="comment-47757697">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/cleverdash">cleverdash</a> 1 day ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">The trend of CLI-first design because AI agents need it is interesting. We ended up in the same place building developer tools, the CLI and API came first because that&#x27;s what agents actually consume. The dashboard came after.<p>The cf permissions check idea from the top comment is great. One thing I&#x27;ve found is that agents are surprisingly good at using CLIs but terrible at diagnosing why a command failed. Clear error messages with the exact fix (&quot;missing scope X, run cf token add --scope X&quot;) matter way more for agent usability than the happy path.</div>
  
  <div class="replies-container" id="replies-47757697"></div>
</div>
